doc.after: In October 2006, Italy accepted delivery of the first C-27J of an initial batch of 12 aircraft.[41] From 12 September 2008 to 27 January 2009, a pair of Italian Air Force C-27Js were deployed to Afghanistan to contribute to NATO in-theatre airlift operations.[42][43] In December 2013, an Italian C-27J was deployed to the Philippines to participate in international humanitarian relief operations in the aftermath of Typhoon Haiyan.[44] The Italian Air Force is also the launch customer for the MC-27J, an armed gunship variant of the C-27J; Italy is the first European nation to operate such an aircraft.[45]
